lead_paragraph: The McXICAN REVOLUTION has not been duly shaped at the hands of the New-Orleans romancers. That there should be an insurrection of the Rio Grande provinces, and an at tempted secession from the federation of four or five of the Northern States, is quite likely, and there is nothing incredible in the rumor that battles have been fought and a general or two demolished.
